# Line endings for the generated realm artefacts.
#
# A realm's .tscn, .json and .navmesh are written by a tool and asserted to
# regenerate BYTE-IDENTICALLY (REALM-C-010), and CI now regenerates every realm
# on Linux and fails on any difference (.github/workflows/realms.yml). That gate
# is only meaningful if a Windows author and a Linux runner agree byte for byte.
#
# Today they do, but by accident: this checkout happens to have core.autocrlf
# true, so the blobs are LF while the working tree is CRLF. Nothing in the repo
# said so, and a contributor with a different setting would have made the check
# fail on every single run — a gate everyone learns to ignore, which is worse
# than no gate.
*.tscn   text eol=lf
*.json   text eol=lf
*.gd     text eol=lf

# Binary, and must never be line-ending converted: a mangled navmesh or mesh
# library is not a diff, it is a corrupt realm.
*.navmesh binary
*.res     binary
*.glb     binary
*.png     binary
*.jpg     binary
